verify real user verify real user groen brothers aviation  wikipedia groen brothers aviation from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from groen brothers aviation inc jump to navigation search groen aeronautics corporation type aircraft manufacturer industry aviation founded  founder david and jay groen headquarters salt lake city utah united states subsidiaries american autogyro website groenaeronauticscom gba founders david and jay groen with hawk  groen aeronautics corporation formerly groen brothers aviation inc is an american autogyro research and development company based in salt lake city utah the company was founded in  by david groen and his late brother jay groen david groen remains the company chairman president and ceo in  time magazine listed gbas hawk gyroplane as one of their featured inventions of the year  contents  history  aircraft flight test programs  aircraft design programs  references  external links historyedit groen brothers aviation started out by incorporating helicopter design components into autogyro design they added helicopterstyle collective pitch control which allowed their aircraft to achieve vertical takeoff and landing and to stabilize flight at high and low speeds the company holds three us patents and several international patents associated with their variable pitch rotor system following the first flight of their proofofconcept aircraft in  the company flew several larger prototype autogyros during the s in september  the company flew their first pistonengine powered prototype of the fourseat hawk  the turbineengined prototype first flew in july  with a rollsroyce   hp  kw turboprop engine and was the world’s first turbine powered gyroplane the designs rotor blades used a companydeveloped natural laminarflow airfoil the hawk  provided perimeter patrol during the  winter olympics in  the company provided the utah olympic public safety command uopsc a hawk  prototype for perimeter patrol around the salt lake city international airport during the  winter olympics and paralympics the hawk  completed  missions over  hours of flying time during the day contract in february  the company introduced its “stabilization augmentation kit” designed to improve inflight stability and safety for kit gyroplanes on the market the company entered the kit market with the sparrowhawk the company discontinued sparrowhawk kit production but formed american autogyro as a subsidiary to produce and sell sparrowhawk kits as a separate business in november  the us defense advanced research projects agency darpa selected a companyled team to design a proofofconcept highspeed longrange vertical takeoff and landing aircraft designed for combat search and rescue the project was named the “heliplane” by darpa and intended to meet economy and performance goals not achievable by existing aircraft the company completed work for phase i of the project in  but the project has not been further funded in december  steve g stevanovich led an acquisition of groen brothers aviation by forming a new private company groen aeronautics corporation which was registered in delaware and acquired all the assets of the public company groen brothers aviation inc this acquisition was accomplished in a transaction equal to more than  million groen brothers aviation inc retains a minority share holding in the groen aeronautics corporation groen aeronautics corporation has since been rebranded as skyworks global inc aircraft flight test programsedit hawk point five single seat gyroplane with collective pitchcontrolled rotor openframe gyroplane first aircraft built by gba citation needed hawk  single seat gyroplane with collective pitchcontrolled rotor retractable landing gear fully enclosed stressed skin monocoque designcitation needed hx sidebyside two seat version of the hawk  gyroplanecitation needed hawk  four seat gyroplane with piston engine designed to meet faa type certification  eventually incorporated a rollsroyce gas turbine engine named the hawk t  revcon x test conversion of a cessna  skymaster airplane this aircraft conversion tested the theory of using fixedwing airplanes as the basic airframes for gyroplanes to reduce cost and shorten development timecitation needed sparrowhawk two seat gyroplane with aluminum frame centerline thrust aircraft widemolded fiberglass cabin with adjustable seating  aircraft design programsedit gba gyroliner commuter airlinercitation needed gba gyrolifter heavylift gyroplanes and gyrodynes of various sizes up to  lbs gvwcitation needed gbadarpa heliplane gyrodyne capable of  mph  nautical miles range hoge at  feet and  °f gba arrowhawk seven seat turboprop gyroplanecitation needed gba shadowhawk tandem two seat gyroplane for aerial observationcitation needed referencesedit  best inventions of  timecom retrieved  january   heliplane globalsecurityorg  scott wb hawk t breathes new life into gyroplanes aviation week  space technology  november  vol  no  pp   best inventions of  timecom  a b one step beyond rotor  wing retrieved  january   groen brother’s aviation us patent and trademark office  garvey w gyrocopters grow up popular mechanics june  pp   “hawk  gyroplane” aerospacetechnologycomunreliable source  “olympic security aided by groen brother’s hawk” aeronews network  “groen brothers announces kit market entry” aeronews network  “darpa funding gyrodyne heliplane rd” defense industry daily  groen aeronautics corporation about gac wwwgroenaeronauticscom retrieved    skyworks global inc  april  groen aeronautics rebranded as skyworks global wwwprnewswirecom retrieved  may   external linksedit official website external video groenaviations channel on youtube retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlegroenbrothersaviationoldid categories helicopter manufacturers of the united statescompanies based in salt lake citydefense companies of the united statesmilitary vehicle manufacturersaircraft manufacturers of the united states establishments in uta